#
#  @effect/cli distinctive features:
#    - HANDLERS RETURN Effect<A, E, R> — every command handler
#      is a typed Effect computation that can fail with type E,
#      depend on services R, and succeed with type A; this means
#      handlers AUTOMATICALLY get structured concurrency,
#      cancellation, retries, error-tracing, and dependency
#      injection from Effect-TS
#    - PIPE-BASED COMPOSITION via Effect-TS's pipe() — commands
#      chain modifiers via `.pipe(Command.withDescription(...),
#      Command.withSubcommands(...), Command.withOption(...))`
#      rather than chained-builder methods
#    - SEPARATE MODULES: `Args` for POSITIONAL args, `Options`
#      for FLAGS, `Command` for command/subcommand definition;
#      `Args.text/integer/boolean/file` + modifiers like
#      `Args.optional`/`Args.repeated`/`Args.withDescription`
#    - ARGS COMBINATORS: `Args.text({name})` + `.pipe(Args.
#      optional, Args.repeated, Args.between(min, max),
#      Args.withDescription(...))`
#    - OPTIONS COMBINATORS: `Options.boolean(name)/text(name)/
#      integer(name)/choice(name, choices)` + `.pipe(Options.
#      withAlias('x'), Options.withDefault(value), Options.
#      withDescription(...), Options.optional)`
#    - TYPE-SAFE HANDLER ARGS — Effect-TS infers the handler's
#      args parameter type from the Args + Options schema; e.g.
#      `Command.make('cmd', { slugOrId, verbose }, ({slugOrId,
#      verbose}) => ...)` — slugOrId is typed as `string`,
#      verbose is typed as `boolean`
#    - SUBCOMMAND TREE via `Command.withSubcommands([cmd1, cmd2])`
#      — composable recursively for arbitrarily-deep nesting
#    - DEPENDENCY INJECTION via Effect's Service pattern —
#      handlers `yield* MyService` to obtain typed services; the
#      runtime layer (`Effect.provide(MyLayer)`) wires the
#      implementations
#    - STRUCTURED CONCURRENCY via Effect fibers — `Effect.gen`
#      and `Effect.race`/`Effect.all` for parallel work; if the
#      CLI is interrupted (SIGINT), running fibers are cleanly
#      cancelled
#    - TYPED ERRORS — `Effect.fail(MyError)` with typed error
#      channel; CLI handler's error type bubbles up to the
#      exit-code mapping (see mx-space's `exitCodeForTag`
#      function that maps typed CLI errors to process exit codes)
#    - PLATFORM ABSTRACTION via `@effect/platform-node`/
#      `@effect/platform-browser` etc. — same CLI can run in
#      node, deno, bun, or browser via swapping the platform
#      layer
#    - AUTO --help / --version generation from Command.make
#      `name`/version + Args/Options descriptions
#    - INSPIRED BY ZIO CLI (Scala), cats-effect (Scala-Haskell),
#      and Haskell's optparse-applicative — @effect/cli brings
#      these algebraic-effect-system CLI patterns into
#      TypeScript via the Effect ecosystem
#  Distinct from R236 commander (TJ chained-builder), R237 oclif
#  (Heroku/Salesforce class-based + decorators), yargs (Bash-
#  style — npm/jest), R398 meow (Sindre zero-config using
#  minimist), R399 minimist (the ORIGINAL), R400 cac (Anthony Fu
#  — uses mri), R403 clipanion (Yarn's class-based with
#  `@Command()` decorators), R406 vercel/arg (spec-object
#  schema with type COERCION FUNCTIONS as types), R409 mri
#  (lukeed minimal parser), R412 citty (UnJS TypeScript-first
#  DECLARATIVE-SCHEMA), R415 cmd-ts (Schniz's PARSER COMBINATOR
#  algebra borrowed from Haskell optparse-applicative — cmd-ts
#  is the CLOSEST RELATIVE to @effect/cli in design philosophy;
#  both are algebraic-functional, but @effect/cli is fully
#  integrated with Effect-TS effect system while cmd-ts is
#  standalone), R418 gluegun (Infinite Red TOOLBOX PATTERN),
#  R422 cleye (privatenumber's type-constructor-as-type-spec),
#  R428 @caporal/core (Mathieu Robin's enterprise framework
#  with integrated logger).  TypeScript-Node documented
#  libraries so far: commander, oclif, yargs, meow, minimist,
#  cac, clipanion, arg, mri, sade, citty, cmd-ts, gluegun,
#  cleye, @caporal/core, @effect/cli (this round)... 17 total.
#  @effect/cli's distinguishing feature vs all other TS-Node
#  libs: @effect/cli is the ONLY ONE that FULLY EMBEDS COMMAND
#  HANDLERS IN AN ALGEBRAIC EFFECT SYSTEM (Effect-TS).  Handlers
#  inherit STRUCTURED CONCURRENCY (fiber-based), DEPENDENCY
#  INJECTION (Layer/Service pattern), TYPED ERRORS (Effect's
#  error channel), and CANCELLATION-SAFETY automatically.
#  @effect/cli's approach: EFFECT-TS-BASED FUNCTIONAL CLI with
#  `Command.make(name, args, handler)` factory + `Args.text/
#  integer/boolean/file` for positionals + `Options.boolean/
